# systemImageNamed(_:)

**Type Method**

Returns an image object that contains the specified system symbol image.

## Declaration

```swift
class func systemImageNamed(_ systemImageName: String) -> Self
```

## Parameters

- **systemImageName**: The name of the system symbol image. Use the [https://developer.apple.com/sf-symbols] app to look up the names of system symbol images.

## Return Value

An object that contains the specified symbol image. If `systemImageName` is invalid, the system passes `nil` to the completion handler of [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INImage/fetchUIImage(completion:)].
